{
  "stem": "18778.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we saw the palm-- my father woke me and we went up on deck and we saw the palm trees-- I had never seen palm trees-- and the pastel-colored houses along the shore and the capital of Havana, which looked a lot like our capitol in Washington, DC.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the harbor patrol came on board.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And passengers had been ordered to get their luggage ready the day before and they were handed all kinds of forms to fill out.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have some of them in my-- in my collection.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And everything was prepared to disembark in Havana.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But then the order came that the ship was not to enter the port, but to throw anchor about a mile or two out of the harbor.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And everybody got very excited and they kept asking the harbor patrol that was on board, when can we get off?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they would say manana.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that went on for a whole week.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A whole week we were in the harbor.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And after a while-- you know, there were lots of families who already had somebody over here, families where the father had already left for the United States and came down to Havana to greet his family or relatives who were in Havana waiting.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And after a while, these people started to rent these little boats and they came out and surrounded the ship and were yelling and shouting and calling for their relatives.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this went on all day long.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was like a circus out there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had cousins on board whose father was here in this country already.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was in Havana to receive them.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
